<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="489" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="0.[151,1437,1395,2033]" pageId="0" pageNumber="489">
<emphasis box="[199,299,1649,1673]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="489" reason="1">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,292,1649,1673]" pageId="0" pageNumber="489">Remark</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
The species is rather variable in its forewing shape and the size of the spots on forewing. However, the genitalic structures display no remarkable differences among the different forms.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="492" pageId="0" pageNumber="489" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="0.[151,1437,1395,2033]" lastBlockId="3.[151,1437,151,895]" lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="492" pageId="0" pageNumber="489">
<emphasis box="[199,316,1721,1745]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="489" reason="1">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,309,1721,1745]" pageId="0" pageNumber="489">Diagnosis</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
The new species is reminiscent superficially of the sympatric 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Oberthur" baseAuthorityYear="1880" box="[1000,1144,1721,1745]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Lemyra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="489" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="jankowskii">
<emphasis box="[1000,1144,1721,1745]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="489">L. jankowskii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[1160,1253,1721,1745]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–8" captionStartId="1.[151,264,1944,1968]" captionTargetBox="[207,1377,184,1907]" captionTargetId="figure-17@1.[194,1393,180,1919]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1–8. Lemyra spp.: adults. Depositories of the specimens: 1–3, 5 and 6 in MWM/ZSM; 4 in ASV; 7 and 8 in NH- MUK." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5119619" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5119619/files/figure.png" pageId="0" pageNumber="489">Figs 3-6</figureCitation>
), but it is distinguished by the somewhat more rounded forewing apex and the wider medial transverse fascia on the forewing. Compared to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Saldaitis, Volynkin &amp; Duda" authorityYear="2018" box="[179,265,1793,1817]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Lemyra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="489" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="elena">
<emphasis box="[179,265,1793,1817]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="489">L. elena</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[279,374,1793,1817]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–8" captionStartId="1.[151,264,1944,1968]" captionTargetBox="[207,1377,184,1907]" captionTargetId="figure-17@1.[194,1393,180,1919]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1–8. Lemyra spp.: adults. Depositories of the specimens: 1–3, 5 and 6 in MWM/ZSM; 4 in ASV; 7 and 8 in NH- MUK." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5119619" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5119619/files/figure.png" pageId="0" pageNumber="489">Figs 7, 8</figureCitation>
), 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Volynkin &amp; Saldaitis" authorityYear="2021" box="[396,471,1794,1817]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Lemyra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="489" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="witti">
<emphasis box="[396,471,1794,1817]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="489">L. witti</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has a somewhat more rounded forewing apex and a pale yellowish hindwing, whereas the forewing of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Saldaitis, Volynkin &amp; Duda" authorityYear="2018" box="[283,369,1829,1853]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Lemyra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="489" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="elena">
<emphasis box="[283,369,1829,1853]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="489">L. elena</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is deep yellow with pink suffusion along the anal margin and sometimes with intense dark grey suffusion medially and subterminally. The male genital capsule of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Volynkin &amp; Saldaitis" authorityYear="2021" box="[833,909,1866,1889]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Lemyra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="489" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="witti">
<emphasis box="[833,909,1866,1889]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="489">L. witti</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[925,989,1865,1889]" captionStart="FIGURES 9–12" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1944,1968]" captionTargetBox="[172,1422,188,1908]" captionTargetId="figure-26@2.[151,1435,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 9–12. Lemyra spp.: male genitalia. Depositories of the specimens dissected: 9 and 10 in MWM/ZSM; 11 in ASV; 12 in NHMUK." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5119621" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5119621/files/figure.png" pageId="0" pageNumber="489">Fig. 9</figureCitation>
) is similar to those of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Oberthur" baseAuthorityYear="1880" box="[1231,1374,1865,1889]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Lemyra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="489" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="jankowskii">
<emphasis box="[1231,1374,1865,1889]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="489">L. jankowskii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 9–12" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1944,1968]" captionTargetBox="[172,1422,188,1908]" captionTargetId="figure-26@2.[151,1435,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 9–12. Lemyra spp.: male genitalia. Depositories of the specimens dissected: 9 and 10 in MWM/ZSM; 11 in ASV; 12 in NHMUK." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5119621" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5119621/files/figure.png" pageId="0" pageNumber="489">Figs 10, 11</figureCitation>
) and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Saldaitis, Volynkin &amp; Duda" authorityYear="2018" box="[280,367,1901,1925]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Lemyra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="489" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="elena">
<emphasis box="[280,367,1901,1925]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="489">L. elena</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[382,462,1901,1925]" captionStart="FIGURES 9–12" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1944,1968]" captionTargetBox="[172,1422,188,1908]" captionTargetId="figure-26@2.[151,1435,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 9–12. Lemyra spp.: male genitalia. Depositories of the specimens dissected: 9 and 10 in MWM/ZSM; 11 in ASV; 12 in NHMUK." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5119621" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5119621/files/figure.png" pageId="0" pageNumber="489">Fig. 12</figureCitation>
), but differs by the somewhat less elongate uncus and the somewhat wider ventral process of the valva. The aedeagus of the new species is very similar to that of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Oberthur" baseAuthorityYear="1880" box="[927,1071,1937,1961]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Lemyra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="489" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="jankowskii">
<emphasis box="[927,1071,1937,1961]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="489">L. jankowskii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and is more elongate than that of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Saldaitis, Volynkin &amp; Duda" authorityYear="2018" box="[151,237,1973,1997]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Lemyra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="489" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="elena">
<emphasis box="[151,237,1973,1997]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="489">L. elena</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The vesica of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Volynkin &amp; Saldaitis" authorityYear="2021" box="[401,476,1974,1997]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Lemyra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="489" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="witti">
<emphasis box="[401,476,1974,1997]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="489">L. witti</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is broader than those of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Oberthur" baseAuthorityYear="1880" box="[741,883,1973,1997]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Lemyra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="489" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="jankowskii">
<emphasis box="[741,883,1973,1997]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="489">L. jankowskii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Saldaitis, Volynkin &amp; Duda" authorityYear="2018" box="[935,1022,1973,1997]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Lemyra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="489" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="elena">
<emphasis box="[935,1022,1973,1997]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="489">L. elena</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; it has a narrow longitudinal cluster of spinules ventrally and a short and relatively narrow dorsal diverticulum bearing a short and narrow cluster of spinules, whereas the vesicae of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Oberthur" baseAuthorityYear="1880" box="[394,535,151,175]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Lemyra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="492" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="jankowskii">
<emphasis box="[394,535,151,175]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="492">L. jankowskii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Saldaitis, Volynkin &amp; Duda" authorityYear="2018" box="[585,670,151,175]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Lemyra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="492" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="elena">
<emphasis box="[585,670,151,175]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="492">L. elena</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
bear a wide cluster of spinules ventrally and a smaller cluster of spinules dorso-laterally (
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Oberthur" baseAuthorityYear="1880" box="[322,464,187,211]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Lemyra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="492" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="jankowskii">
<emphasis box="[322,464,187,211]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="492">L. jankowskii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) or laterally (
<taxonomicName authorityName="Saldaitis, Volynkin &amp; Duda" authorityYear="2018" box="[612,698,187,211]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Lemyra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="492" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="elena">
<emphasis box="[612,698,187,211]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="492">L. elena</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
